Title: Mathu Vadalara 2 Box Office Collection Day 8 Prediction: Sri Simha & Satya's Crime-Comedy Steadily Performs
Content: Mathu Vadalara 2 Box Office Collection Prediction Day 8: Starring Sri Simha and Satya in the lead roles and reprising their characters Babu Mohan and Yesudas, the sequel to the super hit 2019 film 'Mathu Vadalara,' written and directed by Ritesh Rana is titled 'Mathu Vadalara 2.' The movie was released amid low-key promotions on September 13 worldwide. Upon its theatrical release, the movie earned positive reviews from fans and critics.Mathu Vadalara 2 SynopsisIn this sequel to 2019's Mathu Vadalara movie, Babu (Sri Simha) and Yesu (Satya), who were previously delivery agents, are seen as special 'HE Team' agents headed by Deepa (Rohini). Their bad luck follows as they face bigger challenges with exciting and non-stop surprises. The sequel features an additional cast: Sunil, Vennela Kishore, Rohini, and Faria Abdullah.Mathu Vadalara 2 Box Office CollectionMathu Vadalara 2 movie opened to positive reviews at the box office in India and abroad. The movie is continuing to perform steadily with good word-of-mouth and after the first week, the collections started to fall. However, the movie is a profitable venture and is expected to pick up over the upcoming weekend, Check out the day-wise box office collection, below.Day 1: Rs 2.15 CroreDay 2: Rs 3.1 CroreDay 3: Rs 3.5 CroreDay 4: Rs 1.5 CroreDay 5: Rs 1.2 CroreDay 6: Rs 0.8 CroreDay 7: Rs 0.71 CroreDay 8: Rs 0.01 Crore (estimates)Total 8 Days Collection: Rs 12.97 Crore (approximately)Mathu Vadalara 2 CastThe movie stars Sri Simha Koduri as Babu Mohan, Satya as Yesu Dasu, Vennela Kishore as Ravi Teja, Sunil as Michael, Faria Abdullah as Nidhi, Rohini, Ajay as Tejaswi Thota and Ashok, Raja Chembolu, Jhansi, Srinivasa Reddy, and Gundu Sudarshan among others in key roles.Mathu Vadalara 2 CrewWritten and directed by Ritesh Rana, the movie was produced by Chiranjeevi (Cherry) Pedamally and Hemalatha Pedamallu under the Clap Entertainment banner. Mythri Movie Makers came forward to present the movie. Karthika Srinivas and Kaala Bhairava worked as the film's editor and music director respectively.

Title: Emmy Awards 2024: Jeremy Allen White Clinches Second Emmy For Lead Role In The Bear
Content: Jeremy Allen White secured the Outstanding Lead Actor in a Comedy Series award for his role in The Bear at the 76th Emmy Awards. This marks his second consecutive win, with the ceremony held on Sunday, September 15, 2024. "Thank you so much," White expressed during his acceptance speech. "My heart is just beating right out of its chest. Thank you. Thank you to the Academy, my fellow nominees. I'm so honored to be in your company."White faced stiff competition from notable actors including Steve Martin and Martin Short from Only Murders in the Building, D'Pharaoh Woon-A-Tai from Reservation Dogs, Larry David from Curb Your Enthusiasm, and Matt Berry from What We Do in the Shadows. He extended his gratitude to Christopher Storer, the creator of The Bear, acknowledging how the show transformed his life and instilled hope that change is possible when one reaches out.Emmy Awards Presenters and NomineesThe Emmy Awards night featured an impressive lineup of presenters such as Kristen Wiig, Viola Davis, Selena Gomez, Steve Martin, Martin Short, Lily Gladstone, Matt Bomer, Colin Farrell, Mindy Kaling, Jimmy Kimmel, George Lopez, Ebon Moss-Bachrach, Jean Smart, and John Leguizamo. The event was co-hosted by Eugene and Dan Levy and broadcasted live from the Peacock Theater in Los Angeles.Ebon Moss-Bachrach also celebrated a win for Best Supporting Actor for his performance in The Bear. This year's Primetime Emmy nominations were led by FX's Sh≈çgun with 25 nods. The Bear followed closely with 23 nominationsa record for a comedy serieswhile Hulu's Only Murders in the Building received 21 nominations. HBO's True Detective: Night Country garnered 19 nods and Netflix's The Crown earned 18.Record Nominations for Comedy SeriesThe Bear's impressive tally of 23 nominations highlights its significant impact on television comedy. White's heartfelt appreciation extended to his fellow cast members during his speech. "I love you all and hope we can be in each other's lives forever," he said.The annual Emmy Awards continue to celebrate excellence in television by recognising outstanding performances and productions across various genres. This year's event showcased a diverse range of talent and creativity within the industry.White's back-to-back wins underscore his exceptional talent and dedication to his craft. His portrayal in The Bear has not only earned him critical acclaim but also resonated deeply with audiences.

Title: RIP Vikas Sethi: DYK His Role 'Robbie' In K3G Was Originally Offered To THIS Prominent Bollywood Actor?
Content: RIP Vikas Sethi: Vikas Sethi, who is known for playing versatile roles in movies and daily soaps, passed away on September 8 at the age 48. The actor, who had played prominent roles in Kyunkii Saas Bhi Kabhi Bahu Thi, Kahiin To Hoga, Kasautii Zindagi Kay, among others, had also made a mark in Bollywood with popular movies like Kabhi Khushi Kabhie Gham, Oops! among others.However, among all of these, one role that has made a significant mark in audience's heart is his role as 'Robbie', who used to hit Poo(Kareena Kapoor's character) in Kabhi Khushi Kabhie Gham. But do you know the role was initially offered to a prominent Bollywood actor by Karan Johar?Read more: Vikas Sethi's Role In K3G Was Originally Offered To THIS Bollywood ActorWell, not many is aware of the fact that Vikas' role, Robbie, in K3G was originally offered to John Abraham, who hadn't made his debut in Bollywood back then, by Karan Johar. Years later, when John appeared in Koffee With Karan alongside Vivek Oberoi, John opened up about the same.On the other hand, Vikas' role in the movie, 'jispe college ki har ladki marti hain', albeit short, made a significant impact even in today's generation. His iconic dialogue "Hey Poo, movie tonight?" is still famous in reels and on social media.Read more: Vikas Sethi Death ReasonVikas Sethi peacefully died in his sleep followed by a cardiac arrest. He is survived by his wife Jhanvi Sethi and their twin sons, whom they welcomed in 2021. Sharing the picture of his babies, he wrote, "A baby is god's opinion that life should go on.........hip hip hurry."Rest in peace, Vikas Sethi!

Title: EUFF 2024: Lithuanian Filmmaker Tomas Vengris Reveals The Secrets Behind His Cinematic Magic
Content: EUFF 2024 Day 2: Day two of the 29th European Union Film Festival (EUFF) was a whirlwind of emotions, laughter, and thought-provoking cinema. From the comedy-drama "Death is a Problem for the Living" directed by Teemu Nikki, to the romantic-drama "Five and a Half Love Stories In An Apartment In Vilnius, Lithuania" helmed by Tomas Vengris, the day was a rollercoaster of cinematic experiences.After the screening of the film Five and a Half Love Stories in an Apartment in Vilnius, Lithuania, the audience enjoyed an engaging panel discussion featuring Tomas Vengris, the director of the film, and Yile Yara Vianello, actress from the opening film La Chimera. The session was moderated by Padmapriya Janakiraman-founder of Padma's Lit Club, an accomplished dancer, and a seasoned actor with over 15 years in Indian cinema, including lead roles in more than 60 films across six languages.The panel delved into the theme "Longing and Desire: On Screen," with each speaker sharing personal stories that explored the complexities of relationships, love, and the tension between personal dreams and societal pressures. Their insights resonated deeply, leaving a lasting impact on the audience.During the panel, Tomas Vengris, the director of Five and a Half Love Stories in an Apartment in Vilnius, Lithuania, shared how he was drawn to the complex, often absurd emotions within relationships and aimed to bring these to life through his film.He further added that, at some point, he decided to show these stories through the perspective of an apartment, through the POV of a physical building that has been there for centuries and has lived through a million stories, with people who've come in and gone out of it. As per him, this somehow allowed him to step back and reflect on things. According to him, part of working in the comic genre is being able to watch from the side. Drama is when you're looking directly into the perspective, but comedies allow you to step back a little bit, and that gives you the permission to laugh, and by placing the camera in the perspective of the apartment, gave one the permission to laugh. The camera is therefore in another room-behind a shelf, higher up and lower, at every angle so it doesn't feel like a human being is watching the scene. Some of the little dream sequences in the film or interludes were also meant to show the feeling of this apartment's spirit.The 29th European Union Film Festival (EUFF) is currently ongoing in New Delhi till the 16th of November.

Title: Munjya TV Release Date, Channel EXCLUSIVE: Director Aditya Sarpotdar Shares DEETS; Here‚Äôs When, Where To Watch
Content: Munjya TV Premiere Exclusive Update: Munjya, the recent installment in Maddock Films' horror-comedy universe, premiered on June 7 in theatres and has made a significant mark at the box office. As the fourth film in this beloved series, following Stree (2018), Roohi (2021), and Bhediya (2022), it surpassed expectations at the ticket window despite moderate initial buzz.Directed by Aditya Sarpotdar and starring Abhay Verma and Sharvari in the lead roles, has been well-received by both audiences and critics. The film also features Mona Singh, Sathyaraj, and others in key supporting roles. Produced by Dinesh Vijan and Amar Kaushik, it has achieved a significant milestone by crossing the Rs 100 crore mark in domestic box office earnings.MUNJYA TV PREMIERE DATE: DIRECTOR SHARES UPDATE ON FILM'S TV RELEASEAs the film's success continues to create excitement, fans are eagerly awaiting its television premiere. In an exclusive chat with Filmibeat, director Aditya Sarpotdar shared an update on when Munjya will be released on TV.Confirming that Munjya will have its TV premiere before its OTT debut, the filmmaker stated, "Munjya will have its television premiere first and then it'll be releasing on the Disney Plus Hotstar platform. The TV premiere will be on Star Network (Star Gold) and this will be in the last week of August. Immediately after which the film will release on Hostar."HERE'S WHEN border:0; border-radius:3px; box-shadow:0 0 1px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.5),0 1px 10px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.15); margin: 1px; max-width:540px; min-width:326px; padding:0; width:99.375%; width:-webkit-calc(100% - 2px); width:calc(100% - 2px);"> MUNJYA OVERVIEW: ALL ABOUT ITS PLOT AND OTHER DEETSDrawing inspiration from Indian folklore and mythology, Munjya offers a modern reinterpretation of the ancient Brahmarakshas legend. The film breathes new life into traditional myths by introducing a CGI character, skillfully blending age-old elements with a contemporary narrative approach.The story revolves around Bittu, a young boy played by Abhay Verma, who unwittingly unleashes the vengeful spirit of Munjya. This tormented ghost begins haunting Bittu, demanding his help to reunite with his long-lost love, Munni. As Munjya's intense and obsessive quest for love unfolds, the film weaves horror and romance together, creating a unique and captivating tale. By combining folklore with deep emotional themes, Munjya delivers a fresh and engaging twist on the genre.

Title: 70th National Film Awards Timings: When & Where To Watch Prestigious Ceremony Online
Content: 70th National Film Awards Timings: It's a big day for the Indian cinema today. After all, the much talked about and most awaited ceremony is set to take place today. We are talking about the prestigious 70th National Film Awards which will be honouring the finest talent in the Indian cinema. The most await awards ceremony will take place in the national capital wherein President, Droupadi Murmu will be felicitate the winners.When & Where Will 70th National Film Awards Take PlaceTo note, 70th National Film Awards were announced on August 16 this year. However the official ceremony of felicitating the winners will take place on October 8 at the Vigyan Bhavan in New Delhi. It is going to be a starry event as several prominent personalities from Indian cinema will be present at the event along with the winners.70th National Film Awards Timings: Where To Watch Nation Awards 2024 OnlineInterestingly, fans can watch the prestigious 70th National Film Awards online in full HD. Yes! You read it right. The much talked about event will start at 3 PM with the winners gracing the red carpet and 70th National Film Awards will be streamed live on YouTube by DD News Channel.70th National Film Awards Winners70th National Film Awards winners list includes names like Rishab Shetty, Manasi Parekh, Nithya Menen, Arijit Singh, Neena Gupta, A.R Rahman, Pritam, Manoj Bajpayee, etc. Besides, Mithun Chakraborty will also be honoured with Dadasaheb Phakle Award by President Droupadi Murmu.Earlier sharing his feelings on receiving the prestigious Dadasaheb Phalke Award, Mithun Chakraborty told India Today, "Abhi tak hosh sambhala nah (I am still in daze). Such a big award. Main khushi se hass bhi nahi sakta, khushi se ro bhi nahi sakta. (I am totally stunned and I am not out of it yet). Yeh safar bahut katheen tha. Many tell me why I don't make a biography. Main kehta hoon nahi kyunki meri story logo ko inspire nahi karega, unko morally down kar dega. Jo young ladke struggle karte hai unka himmat tod dega. It's so hard, so traumatic, so painful".

Title: Bigg Boss Marathi 5 Elimination Week 5: Varsha, Abhijeet, Or Ankita - Who Will Get Eliminated This Week?
Content: Bigg Boss Marathi 5 Elimination This Week: Bigg Boss Marathi Season 5, with the energetic Riteish Deshmukh as its host, premiered on Colors Marathi in July and swiftly captivated audiences with its compelling content. Title: Indian 2 Advance Bookings: Kamal Haasan-Shankar Sequel's Pre-Sales YET To Begin With Only Four Days To Go...
Content: Indian 2 Advance Bookings Yet To Be Opened: The hyped and much-awaited film Indian2, the epic sequel to the remarkable Indian movie starring Ulaganayagan Kamal Haasan, is going to hit the screens in another four days. The movie written and directed by Shankar Shanmugam is gearing up for a grand theatrical release on July 12 worldwide. The makers of the film are already organizing several pre-release releases across the world.The sequel has locked a runtime of three hours (3 hrs) and will also have another sequel titled Indian 3. Indian 2 will be released in Tamil, Hindi, and Bharateeyudu 2 in Telugu. Indian 2 also marks the first-ever collaboration of Shankar and Anirudh Ravichander.Indian 2 SynopsisSenapathy, shown alive during the climax of the first part, is now in Hong Kong. He decides to return to India after learning that the country is still being overpowered by corruption and injustice.Indian 2 Advance BookingsHonestly, the movie has the potential to draw remarkable openings just like any other big-budget, star-studded, and pan-India film. After a industry-hit like 'Vikram,' Kamal Haasan's Indian 2 is the next big release. However, with poor pre-release buzz for a movie that contains more than five star actors, there is no adequate tension around the release. The buzz, craze, and possible remarkable openings for the film are compromised opine fans. It is just four days until the movie is going to hit the screens worldwide in three languages and the bookings haven't started yet.Indian 2 Cast This vigilante action film sequel stars Kamal Haasan as Veerasekaran Senapathy aka Indian. In addition, the movie stars S.J. Suryah, Kajal Aggarwal, Priya Bhavani Shankar, Rakul Preet Singh, Siddharth, Nedumudi Venu as Krishnaswamy IPS, Kalidas Jayaram, Gulshan Grover, Samuthirakani, Bobby Simha, Brahmanandam, Zakir Hussain, Piyush Mishra, Guru Somasundaram, Delhi Ganesh, Shivaji Guruvayoor, Deepa Shankar, Anant Mahadevan, George Maryan, Vinod Sagar, Akhilendra Mishra, and Benedict Garrett among others in key roles for various versions. Late Vivek, G Marimuthu, and Manobala will be part of the film as the makers wanted to leave their portions intact.Indian 2 CrewWritten and directed by S Shankar, the sequel titled Indian 2 is being helmed by Subaskaran Allirajah and Udhayanidhi Stalin under their Lyca Productions and Red Giant Movies banners on an approximate budget of Rs 250 Crore. Ravi Varma is cranking the camera and A. Sreekar Prasad is the film's editor. Anirudh Ravichander is composing the film's entire background score and music.

Title: The Judge From Hell Last Episode OTT Release Date, Time: When & Where Will Finale Stream Online In India?
Content: The Judge From Hell Last Episode Update: In September this year, Hotstar thrilled K-drama fans with the release of The Judge From Hell, starring popular actors Park Shin-hye and Kim Jae Young. The series was highly anticipated after its announcement, with eager viewers awaiting its arrival.Since its September debut, has quickly gained popularity, especially for its intriguing storyline that mixes romance and suspense. The captivating trailer caught the attention of K-drama enthusiasts worldwide, with a particularly strong fan base emerging in India.The show is finally coming to an end as the last episode of The Judge From Hell is all set to premiere this week and fans across India are excited to watch it online. Here's all you need to know about watching the finale.THE JUDGE FROM HELL LAST EPISODE OTT RELEASE DATE, TIME: HERE'S WHEN TO WATCH IN INDIAThe last episode of The Judge From Hell is set to premiere on November 2, 2024, wrapping up the thrilling journey that has captivated fans. This popular K-drama has maintained a consistent release schedule, with fresh episodes airing every Friday and Saturday at 10:00 PM KST, translating to 6:30 PM IST for Indian viewers.ALSO READ: ALSO READ: With a total of 14 episodes, the series is available in Korean with English subtitles, making it accessible for international viewers eager to immerse themselves in its gripping storyline.PLOT AND CAST OF THE JUDGE FROM HELLIn The Judge From Hell, viewers are taken into the world of supernatural justice through the story of Kang Bit-na, a demon disguised as a judge. With a hidden mission, she seeks out unrepentant criminals, condemning them to eternal punishment. Her journey is one of ruthless pursuit, where she balances her demonic purpose with the complex moralities of justice.Her path crosses with that of Han Da-on, a perceptive detective celebrated for his intuition and heartfelt compassion. Though approachable and calm, Han Da-on's history of personal trauma haunts him, making his private life as complex as his public persona. His ability to crack intricate cases is paired with an emotional depth that gives his character a relatable, human touch.The show seamlessly blends supernatural fantasy with crime investigation, delivering both gripping thriller elements and a layered romantic subplot. Park Shin-hye's portrayal of Kang Bit-na captures her fierce determination, while Kim Jae-young adds depth to Han Da-on, bringing out the intensity of their partnership. Their chemistry fuels the story's emotional impact, drawing viewers deeply into their intertwined destinies.

Title: Kabhi Main Kabhi Tum Today Episode (19) Release Date: When & Where To Watch In India? New Episode Twist
Content: Kabhi Main Kabhi Tum Today Episode (19) Release Date: Bored of the usual melodramatic Hindi dramas that stretch for years? If you have lost interest in shows like Anupamaa, Yeh Rishta Kya Kehlata Hai, Jhanak and Ghum Hai Kisikey Pyaar Meiin, you need to check out Kabhi Main Kabhi Tum.Kabhi Main Kabhi Tum has emerged as a massive success in Pakistan, setting the TRP charts on fire. The show has earned popularity in India, Bangladesh, Turkey, Saudi Arabia and the UAE, courtesy of the intriguing episodes and cripsy storyline. KABHI MAIN KABHI TUM FULL CASTHania Aamir and Fahad Mustafa are back on the small screen with yet another exciting show. They have joined hands for the romantic drama that airs on Monday and Tuesday at 8pm on ARY Digital. The impeccable performances of the lead artists and their sizzling chemistry has worked wonders for KMKT.Here's the full cast of Pakistani show Kabhi Main Kabhi TumFahad Mustafa (Mustafa)Hania Aamir (Sharjeena)Emmad Irfani (Adeel)Javed Sheikh (Iftekhar)Bushra Ansari (Shagufta)Maya Khan (Sidra)Naeema Butt (Rubab)Tauseeq HaiderYousuf Bashir QureshiKABHI MAIN KABHI TUM NEW EPISODE TWIST: WHAT WILL HAPPEN IN SHOW?Sharjeena and Mustafa's relationship has witnessed ups and downs but they are not willing to let anything affect their bond. Despite their rivals trying their best to separate them, the two lovebirds are still together. However, things will change when Mustafa will take a stand for his wife and express displeasure over the way she was treated by his family members.The official Instagram handle of ARY shared a promo to give a glimpse of tonight's episode and the upcoming twist. The caption for the post read, "Will it become difficult for Mustafa and Sharjeena to live together in the house?"WHEN AND WHERE TO WATCH KABHI MAIN KABHI TUM EPISODE 19 IN INDIA?Kabhi Main Kabhi Tum enjoys a significant fan following in the South Asian countries and hence, people in India are keen to watch the show. It is a Pakistani drama, therefore it is only telecast on ARY Digital. The show is also not available on any OTT platform; however, the Indian viewers need not worry.Fans can watch the show without spending a single penny. Yes, you read that right! You can watch the show online free of cost. Read on to know the details.The official YouTube handle of ARY Digital releases the full episodes of Kabhi Main Kabhi Tum after the telecast of the show on TV. Kabhi Main Kabhi Tum episode no. 19 will be released online in the next 2-3 hours on YouTube.

Title: Kanguva Telugu Theatrical Rights: No Telugu Film On October 10 So Far; Mythri Movie Makers Spend Rs 25 Crore!
Content: Mythri Movie Makers Spend Rs 25 Crore On Suriya's Action Drama: Suriya-starrer period action thriller 'Kanguva: A Valiant Saga' which also features Bobby Deol and Disha Patani in pivotal roles is gearing up for a grand theatrical release worldwide for this Diwali on October 10. This action drama was written by Adi Narayana and directed by 'Siruthai' Siva.In this highly anticipated and awaited film, Suriya will be seen in five different roles- Arathar, Venkaater, Mandaankar, Mukaatar, and Perumanathar. The movie will be released in three formats- standard, 3D, and IMAX, giving a variety of movie viewing experience for the film buffs.Kanguva's PremiseKanguva is the story of a warrior who lived in 1678 and died due to a disease. In today's world, a girl is actively researching the disease that killed the warrior of the 16th century.Mythri Movie Makers Spend A BOMB On Kanguva Telugu Rights There are no big releases that have locked October 10 date in Telugu so far. Owing to the craze Suriya and the movie Kanguva has in the two Telugu states, Mythri Movie Makers shelled out huge bucks, about Rs 25 Crore for the film's Telugu theatrical rights, reportedly. Kanguva CastThis Suriya film stars Bollywood actor Disha Patani, Bobby Deol, Yogi Babu, Redin Kingsley, Kovai Sarala, Anandaraj, Ravi Raghavendra, KS Ravi Kumar, Jagapathi Babu, Natarajan Subramaniam, and BS Avinash among other in pivotal characters.Kanguva CrewThe movie was produced by KE Gnanavel Raja, V Vamsi Krishna Reddy, and Pramod Uppalapati under the Studio Green and UV Creations banners. The movie's cinematography is handled by Vetri Palanisamy and Nishadh Yusuf is working as its editor. Devi Sri Prasad is composing the film's entire soundtrack including background score and tunes.

Title: Gully Boy Fame Nakul Roshan Sahdev Lands Key Role In Pratik Gandhi-Starrer For Your Eyes Only

Nakul's involvement in 'For Your Eyes Only' signifies a significant step forward, offering him the opportunity to showcase his talent to a broader, global audience. Viewers can expect a well-crafted storyline and Nakul in a character that will keep them on the edge of their seats. His previous roles have already garnered him recognition, but this project will further establish him as a versatile actor in the competitive world of streaming entertainment.Nakul Roshan Sahdev's involvement is a key highlight, promising fans a memorable and engaging performance. The series is also poised to be a major addition to streaming giant Netflix's roster, and Nakul's role is expected to be a standout feature.As we await the show's release, excitement is building among fans and critics alike. Nakul Roshan Sahdev's addition to the cast not only promises to bring depth and charisma to the series but also highlights his evolving career trajectory. 'For Your Eyes Only' is shaping up to be a landmark project for Nakul, further solidifying his place in the entertainment industry and setting the stage for future success.

Title: Indian 2 Box Office Collection Day 5 Prediction: DROP For Kamal Haasan-Shankar's Sequel In First Week; Deets
Content: Indian 2 Box Office Collection Prediction Day 5: Shankar's directorial Indian 2, featuring Kamal Haasan as one of the most remarkable characters of Indian cinema, Senapathy, was released worldwide on July 12. In Telugu, the movie was dubbed as Bharateeyudu 2 and Hindustani 2 in Hindi. The hyped sequel earned negative response after the theatrical release.Indian 2 Box Office PredictionKamal Haasan's sequel Indian 2, written and directed by Shankar Shanmugam was released to a lukewarm response and negative feedback on July 12 worldwide. The movie was released in three languages and after the first day, bookings declined leading to the film's downfall in terms of box office collection. On the first Monday, the movie almost collapsed. Indian 2 might struggle for achieving break-even. Here is a detail on day-wise box office collection of Indian 2 (India) below.Day 1: Rs 25.6 Crore Day 2: Rs 18.2 CroreDay 3: Rs 15.35 CroreDay 4: Rs 3.2 CroreDay 5: Rs 0.25 Crore (Estimates)Total 5 Days Collection: Rs 62.6 Crore (Approximately)Indian 2 CastThis action film sequel stars Kamal Haasan as Veerasekaran Senapathy aka Indian. In addition, the movie stars S.J. Suryah, Priya Bhavani Shankar, Rakul Preet Singh, Siddharth, Nedumudi Venu as Krishnaswamy IPS, Kalidas Jayaram, Gulshan Grover, Samuthirakani, Bobby Simha, Brahmanandam, Zakir Hussain, Piyush Mishra, Guru Somasundaram, Delhi Ganesh, Shivaji Guruvayoor, Deepa Shankar, Anant Mahadevan, George Maryan, Vinod Sagar, Akhilendra Mishra, and Benedict Garrett among others in key roles for various versions. Late Vivek, G Marimuthu, and Manobala will be part of the film as the makers wanted to leave their portions intact.Indian 2 CrewWritten and directed by S Shankar, the sequel titled Indian 2 is being helmed by Subaskaran Allirajah and Udhayanidhi Stalin under their Lyca Productions and Red Giant Movies banners on an approximate budget of Rs 250 Crore. Ravi Varma is cranking the camera and A. Sreekar Prasad is the film's editor. Anirudh Ravichander is composing the film's entire background score and music.

Title: Ajay Devgn and Rakul Preet Singh To Reunite in Punjab For ‚ÄòDe De Pyaar De 2‚Äô!
Content: Rakul Preet Singh is set to reprise her role in the eagerly awaited sequel 'De De Pyaar De 2', following the success of the first installment. After kick-starting the shoot for 'Son of Sardaar 2', Ajay Devgn will reunite with Rakul for this highly anticipated project. The original film, which also starred Tabu and Jimmy Sheirgill in prominent roles, was a significant commercial success and set the stage for an exciting sequel.In the first 'De De Pyaar De', Rakul Preet Singh and Ajay Devgn's on-screen pairing was a standout. Rakul's portrayal of the lively Ayesha and Ajay's role as the middle-aged Ashish created a fun and engaging chemistry. Their interactions blended romance and comedy, making for a delightful and memorable cinematic experience that resonated with audiences.As per recent reports, a source close to the production team for 'De De Pyaar De 2' has said, "As of now, the production is busy preparing for a 45-50 day schedule in some beautiful and rustic locations in Punjab. While Madhavan, Rakul and the other cast and crew members leave next month for Punjab, Ajay Devgn will be joining after his Son of Sardar 2 schedule which is being filmed in the United Kingdom."The sequel introduces R. Madhavan as Rakul's father, promising an engaging battle of wits between him and Ajay's character, Ashish. Rakul's return to the film is highly anticipated, as her performance in the original was widely praised for bringing charm and adding comedic value to the screen. Fans can look forward to seeing her presence once again in this sequel, as 'De De Pyaar De 2' is slated for release in the summer of 2025.

Title: Sugandha Mishra Says People Called Her Asking 'How I Dared To Insult Legend Like Lata Mangeshkar'
Content: Sugandha Mishra, a name synonymous with versatility in the Indian entertainment industry, has beautifully intertwined her classical music roots with her flair for comedy. Born into the rich musical heritage of the Indore Gharana, Sugandha was rigorously trained in classical music by her grandfather from a tender age. Despite the stringent ban on Bollywood music in her household, Sugandha's creative spirit found its expression in mimicry, a skill she discovered she had a knack for during her college days. "I would mimic people at home as a child, but it wasn't until much later that I realised how much I loved it," she shares, recounting how her mimicry, especially of icons like Lata Mangeshkar, catapulted her into the limelight.Her path, however, was not devoid of challenges. The viral spread of her mimicry act brought not only fame but also criticism, with some accusing her of disrespecting the legendary Lata Mangeshkar. Laughing off the controversy, Sugandha views the incident as a pivotal moment that showcased her talents to a wider audience. Her journey led her from Jalandhar to Mumbai, the city she had longed for since childhood. Here, her unique blend of musical talent and comedic timing won over audiences on platforms like The Kapil Sharma Show and Sa Re Ga Ma Pa. Sugandha credits a significant part of her success to her family's unwavering support, particularly from her uncle, Dr. Arun Mishra.As she reminisced in her interview on Small Towns, Big Stories with Pankaj Dubey, her move to Mumbai marked a significant turn in her career, transforming her into a household name. Despite this, her heart remains tied to her roots in Punjab, whose culture she wishes to further integrate into her work. Mumbai, to Sugandha, is more than just a city of dreams; it's a testament to the manifestation of her aspirations.Sugandha's eclectic taste in entertainment and music mirrors her multifaceted career. She admires Alia Bhatt and the legendary figures of Sridevi and Madhuri Dixit for their acting prowess. In the realm of music, Sonu Nigam and Lata Mangeshkar stand as her inspirations, with their exceptional talent and timeless melodies. Looking ahead, Sugandha is eager to delve deeper into her musical journey, with plans to release an album and complete her doctorate in music at Amritsar University. Her aspirations reflect her enduring passion for music, a core element of her identity that seamlessly blends with her comedic talent.Sugandha Mishra's story, from her disciplined classical training in Jalandhar to becoming a beloved figure in Bollywood, is a testament to the power of perseverance and talent. Her journey is a beacon for aspiring artists from small towns, proving that with passion and the right support, dreams do indeed come true. Her full narrative, filled with laughter, music, and inspiration, is available for viewers on Small Towns, Big Stories on YouTube, where she shares her experiences and hopes for the future.

Title: Yeh Rishta Kya Kehlata Hai Written Update August 9: Kaveri Blames Armaan-Abhira; Rohit Fumes In Anger
Content: Yeh Rishta Kya Kehlata Hai Today Episode: In tonight's (August 9) episode of , Ruhi (Garvita Sadhwani) cries in Rohit's (Romit Raj) arms and apologizes for Armaan (Rohit Purohit) spoiling their date. Meanwhile, Armaan and Abhira (Samridhii Shukla) return on a scooter, stop midway, and argue about the date.YEH RISHTA KYA KEHLATA HAIYEH RISHTA KYA KEHLATA HAI AUGUST 8 WRITTEN UPDATE: ABHIMAAN TEA DATELater, Abhira and Armaan reconcile and have a tea date. Ruhi and Rohit return home, and Vidya and Kaveri wonder why they came back so early. Kaveri questions them and reveals that Abhir and Armaan were also at the restaurant. Vidya blames Armaan and Abhira for ruining Ruhi and Rohit's happiness and date. Manish suggests that there might be some misunderstanding, but Kaveri insists on blaming both of them.Later, Abhira calls the restaurant to inquire about the reservation time that Ruhi made. The restaurant staff informs her that Ruhi booked the table two hours earlier and that Armaan had made his reservation before that. Ruhi pretends to have had a dream where Rohit leaves her, which prompts Rohit to wake up, console her, and assure her that he's not going anywhere.ALSO READ: ALSO READ: ROHIT GETS FURIOUS AFTER SEEING ARMAAN-RUHI TOGETHERRuhi explains to Rohit that she had booked the table, and Rohit blames Armaan's intentions. Ruhi tells him that she felt Armaan was eavesdropping on their conversation, and in a fit of anger, Rohit breaks a vase.Armaan later comes to meet Abhira, and they start arguing again. During this, Armaan notices a wound on Ruhi's hand, and she explains that she got hurt because Rohit broke the vase. Title: Inside Arpita Khan Sharma's Star-studded Birthday Bash: In Pics Salman Khan's Hard-to-miss Banter With Nephew
Content:
Arpita Khan Sharma's Birthday Bash: Arpita Khan turned a year older yesterday and she had a star-studded celebration with her close ones and family. Riteish Deshmukh shared a heart-warming video from the event where Salman Khan, Sohail Khan, Alvira Khan along with Arpita's husband, Ayush Sharma were present. However, it's Salman's funny banter with Arpita Khan's, Ahil, which stole the heart for many.Read more: Salman Khan's Funny Banter With Arpita Khan Sharma's Son Ahil On Her BirthdaayThe video was shared by Riteish Deshmukh on his Instagram story where Arpita Khan Sharma could be seen cutting a three tier cake as Ayush Sharma, her daughter Aayat, Salman Khan, Sohail Khan, Alvira Khan Agnihotri, and Ahil were seen. While Arpita was cutting the cake, Salman could be seen teasing nephew Ahil, who was beside him, with his elbow.
The video ended with as Arpita cut the cake and feed it to her husband Ayush, Salman, Sohail, and their mother, Salma Khan. She later feed it to Alvira as well. For the bash, Riteish Deshmukh and Genelia D'souza were also invited. Sharing the video, Riteish wrote, "Happy Birthday My dearest darling Arpita Khan Sharma- We love you!! Have a fabulous year ahead!!!!"Read more: Arpita Khan got married to Ayush Sharma November, 2014 after dating for years. The duo became parents to son Ahil, in March, 2016, and daughter Ayaat in December, 2019. To note more, Salman Khan shares his birthday with niece, Ayaat.More About Salman KhanOn the other hand, Salman Khan was last seen in Tiger 3 with Katrina Kaif where he reprised his role after years. He will be next seen in Sikander, helmed by AR Murugadoss. The film will also star Rashmika Mandanna.

Title: Jani Master Case: Choreographer Gets Conditional Bail But Is NOT Working For Allu Arjun's Pushpa 2
Content: Jani Master Gets Conditional Bail: After facing several bail appeals that have been rejected, Jani Master, a popular choreographer in the South Indian film industry, finally got bail on conditions. The Telangana High Court granted bail to the Dance master in the sexual harassment case filed under the POCSO Act. The celebrity choreographer rose to popularity after composing dance moves for Thalapathy Vijay, Ram Charan and Allu Arjun. He then went on to work with Salman Khan among others in Bollywood. For his composition of the 'Megham Karukatha' song from Thiruchitrambalam featuring Dhanush and Nithya Menen, he was awarded a National Award for Best Choreography. However, the sexual harassment case prompted the government to revoke the award. Jani Master Loses Opportunity To Work With Allu Arjun On Pushpa 2's Special SongSpeaking at the press meet that was held a while ago in Hyderabad, the makers at the helm of Mythri Movie Makers clarified that there are going to start shooting of the special song from November and another Choreographer has been roped in for it. He earlier composed 'Buttambomma' for Allu Arjun, one of his most popular compositions.Sexual Harassment Case on Jani MasterIn her complaint, Jani Master's assistant choreographer and victim stated, "I met him in 2017 and joined his group in 2019. During a shoot in Mumbai, he forced himself upon me. He threatened to have me removed from the project as well as ensure that I didn't get any work thereafter. I continued to work in his team but whenever there was an opportunity he used to force me to get physical with him. In one such instance, he even hit my head on the mirror inside a caravan. I left his team and tried to work independently. He then started to attack me verbally and barged into my house along with his wife. They ransacked my house and forced me to marry him. "

Title: Ishq Jabariya Actress Siddhi Sharma Shares Her Plan B If Acting Career Didn't Work: Would Have Become...
Content: Actress Siddhi Sharma, known for her role as Gulki in Sun Neo's "Ishq Jabariya," recently shared her thoughts on what career path she might have taken if acting hadn't worked out. She revealed that dancing and modeling were her other passions.Siddhi Sharma's Creative Pursuits"If I weren't an actor, I'd definitely be a dancer or a model. I've always loved being in the creative field because dancing and modeling are where my passions lie. Before I got into acting, I spent a lot of time dancing and modeling, which I really enjoyed. Back in school, I was fascinated by fashion design, but when I got to college, I started exploring theater and practicing my dancing even more. If acting hadn't worked out for me, I would have pursued a career in dance or modeling without a second thought," Siddhi Sharma shared.Her love for creativity extends beyond acting. She finds joy in expressing herself through movement and style. "Creativity has always driven me, and I find joy in expressing myself through movement and style. Whether I'm on stage or in front of the camera, I love the thrill of performance. Bringing something to life and sharing that with an audience is what makes every moment special for me," she added.The Journey of Ishq Jabariya"Ishq Jabariya," airing on Sun Neo, tells the story of Gulki (played by Siddhi Sharma), a lively young woman aspiring to become an air hostess. The narrative unfolds with unexpected twists as she navigates various challenges. The show also features Kamya Panjabi and Lakshay Khurana in significant roles.Before settling on acting, many individuals explore different activities to discover their true potential. This exploration not only helps them understand their creative talents but also provides a backup plan if their initial goals don't pan out. Siddhi Sharma's journey is a testament to this process.For those interested in following Gulki's adventures, "Ishq Jabariya" airs on Sun Neo from Monday to Saturday at 7:30 PM.Siddhi's reflections highlight how important it is to have multiple interests and skills. Her passion for dance and modeling showcases her versatility and dedication to the creative arts.Exploring various hobbies can lead to discovering hidden talents and potential career paths. For Siddhi Sharma, these explorations played a crucial role in shaping her career choices.The actress's journey from fashion design fascination in school to theater exploration in college illustrates the diverse paths one can take before finding their true calling.Ultimately, Siddhi Sharma's story emphasizes the importance of pursuing one's passions and having alternative plans ready if needed.

Title: Jigra Box Office Collection Day 5 (Early Updates): Alia‚Äôs Film Struggles In Week 1; Inches Close To 20Cr
Content: Jigra Box Office Collection Day 5 (Early Updates): Alia Bhatt has come with the first release of the year and it has been all over the headlines. We are talking about Jigra which is helmed by Vasan Bala and has presented Alia in a never seen before avatar. Also starring Vedang Raina along with Sobhita Dhulipala, Manoj Pahwa, etc in key roles, Jigra has managed to create a massive buzz in the town with its trailer and songs. Interestingly, Jigra has been one of the most anticipated releases of the year and has hit the screens on October 11For the uninitiated, Jigra marks Alia's first collaboration with Vedang and the duo plays the role of siblings in the movie. To note, Jigra revolves around a young girl Satya (played by Alia Bhatt), whose younger brother Ankur (played by Vedang Raina) is stuck in a foreign jail and is being tortured there. And thus begins her challenging journey to free her brother. Jigra speaks volumes about the unconditional love between siblings and Alia did leave a mark with her impressive performance.Jigra Box Office Collection Day 4Jigra, which opened to decent reviews, made an opening box office collection of Rs 4.55 crores. While the movie did see a hike during the opening weekend, the first Monday has witnessed a massive drop in collections. According to a report published in Sacnilk, Jigra raked in Rs 1.65 crores on day 4 (first Monday) which took the overall collections of the movie to Rs 18.25 crores.Jigra Box Office Collection Day 5 (Early Updates)Given the ongoing trends, Jigra will be seen struggling at the box office in the first week. The movie has made a collection Rs 99 lakhs today (day 5/ first Tuesday) so far (at 7:27PM). As of now, Jigra's overall collections stand at Rs 19.24 crores and it is evident that the movie is inching towards Rs 20 crores mark.Jigra vs Vicky Vidya Ka Woh Wala Video: Which Film Is Leading At Box OfficeInterestingly, Jigra is witnessing a box office clash with Rajkummar Rao and Triptti Dimri starrer Vicky Vidya Ka Woh Wala Video. While both the films have opened to mixed reviews, Jigra has failed to beat Vicky Vidya Ka Woh Wala Video so far at the box office. It will be interesting to see if Alia's film will manage to pick up pace in the coming days

Title: &TV Launches A Compelling Social Drama ‚ÄòBheema‚Äô Centered On Equal Rights
Content: National, 1st Aug 2024: Set in the 1980s, &TV's new show 'Bheema ', produced by Raj Khatri Productions, follows the story of a young girl named 'Bheema' from the other community. The story is a social drama focusing on this young girl's predicament and her journey toward equal rights. The audience will witness her courageous journey as she battles adversities stemming from her family, society, and economic conditions. Despite facing numerous injustices and discrimination, she fearlessly strives to overcome these obstacles. Bheema's resolve to uphold the laws and ideals of Dr B.R. Ambedkar, the architect of the Indian constitution, is a testament to her unwavering commitment despite the challenges. At a tender age, she dedicates herself sincerely to this mission. However, the dominant class in society, threatened by her pursuit, unites with unprecedented force to thwart her efforts. Yet, Bheema's determination remains unshaken, even as obstacles mount, intensifying the conflict.Talking about the show, Vishnu Shankar, Business Head - &TV, says, "The resounding success of our shows 'Ek Mahanayak-Dr B.R. Ambedkar' and 'Atal' is a testament to stories of hope and resilience resonating well with our viewers. Our latest offering, 'Bheema', follows the journey of a young girl named Bheema, showcasing her fight for equal rights, her trials and tribulations and her aspirations for recognition and social change. The story will depict a compelling narrative of overcoming societal barriers by highlighting the universal themes of hope, determination, and transformation. Bheema's challenges and triumphs will resonate with viewers, making her journey both inspiring and relatable. It will also provide a powerful lens through which viewers can explore their values and beliefs, making for engaging and thought-provoking storytelling."Raj Khatri, Producer, Raj Khatri Productions, comments, "Bheema is an appealing story of resilience, determination and aspirations. This show is the perfect blend of emotions and aesthetic production that caters to the growing appetite for quality content amongst TV audience. I also extend my heartfelt appreciation to &TV for consistently delivering compelling narratives and providing our show a platform to connect meaningfully with audiences nationwide. The story of Bheema strives to inspire, provoke thought and reinforce the power of storytelling to foster empathy and understanding."Shanti Bhushan, Writer of Bheema , adds, "The social drama set in the 1980s within a quaint village in Uttar Pradesh has been crafted with artistic flair, vividly resurrecting an era that resonates with its audience. Each character is meticulously developed, ensuring every scene resonates deeply. Bheema's character is poised to ignite reflection and elevate social drama to new heights of success."Talking about her title role in Bheema, Tejaswini Singh says, "Bheema is courageous and determined to pursue education. She believes in standing up for the right despite facing numerous difficulties. It is an inspiring and powerful character, and I am very excited to play the title role. I hope people like our show as much as we are enjoying shooting for it."Smita Sable , essaying Bheema's mother Dhaniya, adds, "The appealing storyline of Bheema will attract viewers' attention. As an actor, we strive to bag roles which are meaningful and create a long-lasting impact. Dhaniya is a caring mother who keeps her family together. She understands the significance of education and advocates for Bheema's right to education."On playing Bheema's father, Mewa, Amit Kumar comments, "Mewa is a simple person who wishes well for everyone and is always willing to help people. However, his weakness lies in his inability to speak out against injustice even when it affects him. The nuanced portrayal of Mewa and the captivating narrative of Bheema made me instantly sign for the show."Tune in to watch 'Bheema', premiering on August 6th at 8:30 pm, every Monday to Friday only on &TV!

Title: Do Patti: Did You Know Actor Shaheer Sheikh Is Known As The 'Shah Rukh Khan‚Äò Of THIS Country
Content: Actor Shaheer Sheikh is currently basking success of Do Patti where he impressed the audience as Dhruv Sood. Recently, Do Patti stars visited 'The Kapil Sharma Show' where the host Kapil Sharma spilled the beans on how Shaheer Sheikh is known as 'Shah Rukh Khan of Indonesia'.Why Is Shaheer Sheikh Known As The Shah Rukh Khan Of Indonesia?Shaheer laughed at this and shared the anecdotes behind this. The Mahabharat actor said, "Shah Rukh Khan is a huge star over there. Every person knows him well. For them, India is represented by Shah Rukh Khan. So, when my show became popular and I did a couple of movies, they started calling me the Shah Rukh Khan of Indonesia."Shaheer Sheikh is a well known name who is recognized globally after his performance And role as Arjuna rose to fame for the superhit television show 'Mahabharat' (2013). His impeccable performance undoubtedly made the actor an overnight sensation and a household name for all the right reason. After this, his fan base continued to grow and not to mention he also built a loyal fan base for him in the Indonesian entertainment segment.Not many know the fact that Shaheer also starred in popular Indonesian TV series such as Cinta di Langit Taj Mahal and Roro Jonggrang, where he was seen playing lead roles. Other than these, he also hosted numerous reality and variety shows, including Panah Asmara Arjuna and Asia's Got Talent, where he was seen as a guest.On the work front, Shaheer is currently seen in Do Patti alongside Kajol and Kriti Sanon, who also turned producer for the movie. Talking about her experience as producer, Kriti said, "It's amazing, yeah. It's amazing to just get into every part of the process of filmmaking. I think I remember, you know, now when I look back, like during Heropanti, when I came on set, I was like this curious child on the set who was like, 'Yeh nakli hai?', 'Yeh mombatti hai?', 'Yeh kiya hai'. And I didn't know what was real and what wasn't."

Title: Singham Again vs Bhool Bhulaiyaa 3 Box Office Report Day 1: Kartik‚Äôs Film BEATS Ajay‚Äôs Film In Morning Shows
Content: Singham Again vs Bhool Bhulaiyaa 3 Box Office Report Day 1: Ajay Devgn is making headlines for his second box office clash of the year. After his Auron Mein Kahan Dum Tha clashed with Ulajh, his cop drama Singham Again is locking horns with Kartik Aaryan starrer Bhool Bhulaiyaa 3 and the audience is quite excited about the same. While Singham Again is a cop drama, Bhool Bhulaiyaa 3 is a horror comedy and both films are the third installment of their respective franchise and have managed to create a substantial buzz in the town.Directed by Rohit Shetty, Singham Again is the fifth addition to the cop universe after Singham, Singham Again, Simmba and Sooryavanshi. Apart from Ajay, Singham Again also features Arjun Kapoor, Deepika Padukone, Ranveer Singh, Akshay Kumar, Tiger Shroff and a cameo by Salman Khan. On the other hand, Bhool Bhulaiyaa 3 is helmed by Anees Bazmee and features Kartik reprising his role as Rooh Baba along with Triptii Dimri, Vidya Balan, Madhuri Dixit, Rajpal Yadav etc in the lead.Singham Again Morning Show Occupancy Day 1Despite the substantial buzz, Singham Again got a slow occupancy for the morning shows in India. According to a report published in Sacnilk, Singham Again recorded an occupancy of 39.39% for the morning shows.Bhool Bhulaiyaa 3 Morning Show Occupancy Day 1On the other hand, Kartik's Bhool Bhulaiyaa 3 recorded a decent occupancy for the first show. According to Sacnilk, Bhool Bhulaiyaa 3 will record 50.67% occupancy for the morning shows.Bhool Bhulaiyaa 3 BEATS Singham Again Occupancy Day 1It is evident that Bhool Bhulaiyaa 3 has witnessed more footfalls than Singham Again in the morning shows and seems to be quite popular among the audience. However, the box office reports suggests that Singham Again (Rs 16.27cr) is leading over Bhool Bhulaiyaa 3 (Rs 12.96cr) until 2:47 PM. Let us know in the comment section which film are you supporting.

Title: Is Arjun Rampal Secretly Married To Girlfriend Gabriella Demetriades? Actor Says, "We Are Already Married...."
Content: Arjun Rampal is considered one of the hotties in B'town and her female fans had quite a lot of interest in his personal life! However, before he made it big in Bollywood, he was already married to Mehr Jesia. But the marriage fell into the pit and the duo got divorced after 2 decades. Arjun, on the other hand, found love in Gabriella Demetriades with whom he shares two children out of wedlock.Is Arjun Rampal Secretly Married To Gabriella Demetriades?Recently, talking about it in an interview, when Arjun was asked about his wedding plan, he said that they are 'already married'. Elaborating how that happened, he said, "Marriage is just a piece of paper. We are already married, and there is no doubt about that in my mind. But sometimes what that piece of paper can do is change you. You're just legally bound in a way, but it could change your attitude towards each other. In both our minds, we are married to each other..."Talking further, Arjun also revealed that Gabriella and Mehr share a very good bond, "I have two beautiful boys with her. I am blessed. My daughters and her (Gabriella) get along beautifully. Mehr and her (Gabriella) get along."Arjun Rampal Calls Himself 'Idiot' When Speaking About Divorcing Mehr JesiaHe said while taking the responsibility, "I come from a broken home when I was young, and for me to not have succeeded in marriage was something which I really had to look back upon and see how did this go wrong and how did I not see... then I realised why it went wrong and what were the things, and I take responsibility for it."He further added, "Today, we all are very close and loving towards each other... I got married when I was 24, and I think it is too early; you're too young, and there's a lot to learn and experience. You have to become mature. Guys mature far slower than women do. It's a proven fact that we are idiots. If you want to be successful in it (marriage), wait it out."Arjun Rampal and Mehr Jesia got married in 1998 and got divorced in 2019. The duo share two daughters- Myra and Mahikaa. On the other hand, Arjun and Gabriella started dating in 2018 and they had welcomed sons- Arik and Ariv.

Title: Samantha Reacts To SCIENCE ILLITERATE Comments; Says 'Had To Take Many Types Of Medicines That Worked For Me'
Content: Samantha Supports Her Post On Hydrogen Peroxide Nebulizer: Samantha, the sultry actress who has been active on her social media handles of late discussing health and mental well-being, became a subject of trolls after her 'alternative nebulizer' hack went viral drawing flak from the doctors' community.In response, the Citadel actress, who is also an entrepreneur supported her stand and clarified, "Over the last couple of years, l've had to take many different types of medicines. I've tried everything I was strongly advised to take. As advised by highly qualified professionals and after doing as much self research as is possible for a lay person like me.Many of these treatments were also very very expensive. I would always keep thinking about how fortunate I am that I could afford it and about all those who cannot. And for the longest time, conventional treatments weren't making me better. There's a good chance it was just me and am sure they will work very well for others.These two factors led me to also read up on alternate therapies and treatments. And after trial and error, I found treatments that worked wonderfully for me. Treatments that also cost a fraction of what / was spending on conventional healthcare.I am not naive enough to go about strongly advocating a treatment. / merely suggested with good intention because of all that I have faced and learnt in the last couple of years. Especially that treatments can be financially draining and many may not be able to afford them. End of the day, we all depend on educated doctors to guide us. This treatment was suggested to me by a highly qualified doctor who is an MD, who has served DRDO for 25 years. He, after all his education in conventional medicine, chose to advocate an alternate therapy.A certain gentleman has attacked my post and my intentions with rather strong words. Said gentleman is a Doctor too. I have no doubt that he knows more than I do. And I am quite sure his intentions were noble. It would have been kind and compassionate of him had he not been so provocative with his words. Especially the bit where he suggests I should be thrown in prison. Never mind. I suppose it goes with the territory of being a celebrity. I posted as someone who needs medical treatments and not as a celebrity. And I certainly am not making any money from the post nor endorsing anyone. I was merely suggesting a treatment as an option after undergoing it myself, for others who may be looking for options because conventional medicine isn't working for them. Especially more affordable options.We cannot just give up when medicines aren't working. I certainly wasn't ready to give up...Coming back to the topic of the said gentleman Doctor, it would have been nice had he politely invited my Doctor, whom I have tagged in my post, rather than go after me. I would have loved to have learnt from that debate and discussion between two highly qualified professionals.And as far as sharing information about the treatments that have helped my health, I shall be more careful as my intentions are only to help others. Not to harm anyone. I've had so many well meaning people suggesting ayurveda, homeopathy, acupuncture, Tibetan medicine, pranic healing etc. I heard them all out. I was merely doing something similar. Sharing something that worked for me, as an option. And I know many of us dealing with health issues need that help, especially given how overwhelming it is when every option has qualified people who are so certainly sure of their polar opposite opinions. Both sides, for and against every treatment, are both so sure and persuasive. It's difficult to navigate these and find good help,(sic)."After the actress posted a picture of herself trying the 'alternative medicine hack' which is also cost-effective. She said, "Before taking medication for a common viral, consider trying an alternative approach. One option is to nebulize with a mixture of hydrogen peroxide and distilled water. Works like magic. Avoid unnecessary use of tablets." She also tagged a doctor's Instagram handle along with her post.The Liver Doc is one of the first to react to her post and said "Influential Indian actress Ms Samantha Ruth Prabhu, who is, unfortunately, a health and science illiterate, advises millions of her followers to inhale hydrogen peroxide to prevent and treat respiratory viral infections,(sic)." He also suggested that hydrogen peroxide nebulization is life-threatening. He shared a picture and a link to the advice by a US-based organization which reads, "Do not put hydrogen peroxide into your nebulizer and breathe it in. This is dangerous. It is not a way to prevent nor treat COVID-19."

Title: The Greatest of All Time OTT Release: When And Where To Watch Vijay's Movie Online After Its Theatrical Run
Content: The GOAT OTT Release: "The Greatest of All Time (GOAT)" is a Tamil sci-fi action film featuring Vijay in dual roles. Directed by Venkat Prabhu and produced by AGS Entertainment, this marks the studio's 25th production. Notably, it is Vijay's penultimate film before his anticipated political debut, with its global theatrical release on September 5, 2024.Netflix secured the streaming rights for the film, acquiring the Tamil, Telugu, Malayalam, and Kannada versions for ‚Çπ125 crore (US$15 million) and the Hindi version for ‚Çπ25 crore (US$3 million). Zee Tamil obtained the satellite rights for ‚Çπ93 crore. During the film's promotional campaign, Venkat Prabhu announced that a director's cut, featuring approximately 20 minutes of additional content, will be released on Netflix after the theatrical run. Typically, films are available on OTT platforms about 4 to 5 weeks after their theatrical release.GOAT SynopsisGandhi, a hostage negotiator, field agent, and spy with Chennai's Special Anti-Terrorist Squad (SATS), collaborates closely with RAW. A devoted family man with a wife and son, he encounters new challenges years after his retirement. Together with his SATS team, consisting of himself and three other members, Gandhi must confront and rectify the repercussions of their past missions.GOAT Cast And CrewThe cast of The Greatest of All Time (GOAT) features Vijay in dual roles as Gandhi and Jeevan, with Akhil portraying the younger Jeevan. Supporting roles include Prashanth, Prabhu Deva, Ajmal Ameer, Mohan, and Jayaram. Sneha plays Gandhi's wife and Jeevan's mother, while Laila is cast as a doctor and Meenakshi Chaudhary as Srinidhi, Jeevan's love interest, whose voice is dubbed by M. M. Manasi. Vaibhav appears as Jeevan's friend, and Premgi Amaren as Gandhi's brother-in-law and Jeevan's uncle. The ensemble also includes Yugendran, Parvati Nair, VTV Ganesh, Aravind Akash, Ajay Raj, Komal Sharma, Abyuktha Manikandan, Anjena Kirti, Dileepan, Ganja Karuppu, T. Siva, and Irfan Zaini, with Vijayakanth and Y. G. Mahendran making cameo appearances, the latter using AI technology for his role.Directed by Venkat Prabhu, who co-wrote the screenplay with Ezhilarasu Gunasekaran and K. Chandru and wrote the dialogues with Viji, GOAT is produced by Kalpathi S. Aghoram, Kalpathi S. Ganesh, and Kalpathi S. Suresh under AGS Entertainment. The film features cinematography by Siddhartha Nuni, editing by Venkat Raajen, and a soundtrack by Yuvan Shankar Raja.

Title: Do Patti Streams On Netflix: Is Kriti Sanon & Kajol Starrer Worth A Watch? What Do Netizens Say? Take A Look!
Content:
Do Patti Streams On Netflix: Kajol, Kriti Sanon and Shaheer Sheikh starrer Do Patti released today and the film seems to have impressed audiences amidst mixed reviews. Kajol plays a cop for the very first time in a career span of three decades and has created magic on screen. Netizens are all praises for the movie.Is Do Patti Worth A Watch? Here's What Netizens SayNetizens who have taken to X have written,"Do Patti is a must watch+ a neat story, stellar cast and beautiful story of mother -daughter and domestic violence. Kajol ma'am what a performance ever means from Baazigar to Do Patti in fact she's so amazing performance."Another user wrote, " Just finished watching #DoPatti! This movie is so so good! Kriti Sanon nailed it as Saumya and Shailee. Kajol was great. The message of this film is so so important. Please do watch it. It should reach the audiences. Could've released in the theatres, it's phenomenal."Another user wrote,"Kajol as Vidya Jyoti in Do Patti is fierce, fearless and phenomenal! Queen! your intensity and performance shines!"
More About Do PattiDo Patti is directed by Shashank Chaturvedi and is produced by Kanika Dhillon under her banner Kathha Pictures in association with Kriti Sanon 's Blue Butterfly Films. Earlier, talking to Zoom entertainment, Kriti Sanon said, "I was emotionally invested (in Do Patti). I don't think I ended up detaching myself. It started with the fact that I wanted to produce something and tell a story that talks about this subject a little more deeply. A lot of films have been done well but I felt there was a lot more depth in it and it had to be hard-hitting. It is a hard-hitting reality and it is getting worse. The idea was to do it as sensitively as we could without shying away from really showing and talking (about domestic violence)."She further added, "When you do those scenes, it is not possible for it to not affect you at all. It does affect you. You have to feel it, go through it and move on. That is just a scene and I know that. But, that's someone's reality. That is scary."

Title: Yek Number OTT Release EXCLUSIVE! Sayli Patil Reveals Why She Signed Film & Found Her Character Appealing
Content: Yek Number OTT Release on ZEE5: Sayli Patil is on cloud nine as she has received critical acclaim for her performance in Yek Number. As the film had its world digital premiere on ZEE5, the actress interacted with Filmibeat and spoke about her character, sharing the reason why she signed the film.Here are excerpts from the interview-1. What appealed to you about your character and the story that made you say yes to this film?Ans: The character Pinky is a strong and firm girl who truly stands out because of her clear thought process and deep devotion to her idol Raj Thackeray and his ideology, and I love that she's headstrong and unafraid to be different. The story itself was incredibly engaging, it conveyed exactly the thoughts and emotions it needed to with great impact. I felt the idiology, the whole team, role, paired with such a powerful narrative, was something I absolutely wanted to be a part of.2. Yek Number has a unique blend of love, romance and social themes. How did you approach your character to bring out the authenticity of the character?'Ans: While Shooting Yek Number is focused on learning the details of the language and its dialects so I could portray the characters better. I also had the opportunity to narrate the film, which allowed me to connect even more with the story and its themes. which was a significant aspect of the film's authenticity and the character. Speaking the language naturally helped me connect better with my co-stars and the crew, creating a more authentic environment on set.3. Could you share any personal challenges you faced while preparing for this role? Was there a particular scene or emotion that was difficult to capture?Ans: Fortunately, everything felt simpler because of the supportive team, Rajesh sir's clear direction, and the freedom he gave me to bring my own personality into Pinky's character. Pinky is a completely different person by the end of the film, so to show that change, I prepared her mood and mindset before each scene. This approach helped me bring out her layers and capture her growth on screen.

Title: NBK 50 Years Celebrations: Jr NTR UNINVITED For Golden Jubilee Celebration Event of Nandamuri Balakrishna?
Content: Jr NTR Uninvited For NBK 50 Years Celebration? Nandamuri Balakrishna, the son of the legendary, late Nandamuri Taraka Rama Rao (NTR), one of the pillars of the Telugu film industry and politician who served as the CM under his Telugu Desam Party (TDP), is celebrating 50 years in Tollywood. The massive achievement is going to be celebrated on a large scale with the who's who of the Telugu, Kannada, Malayalam, Tamil, and Hindi industries coming together.The Golden Jubilee celebrations event is being held on September 1 at the Novotel HICC in Hyderabad and the heads of all the filmmaking departments have pitched in to look into the arrangements. Apart from the plethora of actors who are from the current generation to the people who worked with Balayya since his debut, the extravagant event is also going to see politicians and Chief Ministers of the Telugu-speaking states coming under the roof.As the preparations have come to an end, we hear that the organizers have not invited Jr NTR, Balakrishna's elder brother Hari Krishna's son to the event. According to the latest insider buzz from Tollywood, Jr NTR was not invited to the event which is nothing but solidifying the internal clashes that the Nandamuri family are holding onto.Jr NTR & Nandamuri Kalyan Ram To Stay Away?While other star heroes are invited and they RSVPed, it is believed that Jr NTR and his half-brother Nandamuri Kalyan Ram, who also didn't receive an invitation to the event, will stay away from it. The brothers have come close and have stuck together ever since the death of their father Hari Krishna and another brother Janaki Ram.Recently, at the condolence meeting held for Taraka Ratna, videos of Nandamuri Balakrishna ignoring Jr NTR on purpose surfaced online, much to the disappointment of the Nandamuri fans. Jr NTR, who earlier was always cheering and openly speaking about his affection for Balayya Babai is maintaining a distance of late.Fans of Jr NTR opined that Jr NTR was different at that time when he campaigned for TDP and Chandra Babu Naidu trying to get close to the Nandamuri family. Now, he is different and has been keeping himself at bay from the political and familial associations after his father's death.Mega Family & Allu Family Heroes On A Single StageMeanwhile, Tollywood is curious about the coming together of Allu Arjun and the mega heroes headed by megastar Chiranjeevi for the 'NBK 50 Years In TFI' celebrations. Chiranjeevi is anyway going to attend the event because he and NBK belong to a generation and are friends. Allu Arjun, who received the invitation gave his green signal.Allu Arjun's fans and mega fans are always debating on the social media handles of late and Allu Arjun's stand for his friend during the election campaign irked the mega fans. But there have been fissures in the mega and Allu compounds even before.On the work front, Jr NTR is working on the last leg of Devara Part 1 with Janhvi Kapoor under the direction of Koratala Siva. He is expected to join the sets of NTRNEEL in the last week of September. After 'Bhagavanth Kesari,' another action entertainer referred to as NBK 109 by Bobby Kolli is under the making for Nandamuri Balakrishna.

Title: Lawrence Bishnoi Hit List: After Salman Khan, Why Is Lawrence Bishnoi Gang After BB17 Winner Munawar¬†Faruqui?
Content: Why Is Bigg Boss 17 Winner Munawar Faruqui On Lawrence Bishnoi Hit List: Lawrence Bishnoi and his gang are all over the news lately. From planning attacks on Bollywood superstar Salman Khan to brutally killing former minister of Maharashtra and NCP leader Baba Siddique, the notorious gang has been all over the list. Now, according to reports, the notorious jailed gangster Lawrence Bishnoi had also planned to kill popular stand-up comedian and Bigg Boss 17 winner Munawar Faruqui. But why is Munawar on the Bishnoi gang's target list? Read on...Lawrence Bishnoi Hit List: After Salman Khan, Why Is Munawar Faruqui On Bishnoi Gang's Target List? The notorious gang of has been after superstar Salman Khan since years now. Earlier in April this year, several rounds of bullets were fired outside Khan's residence in Mumbai, Galaxy Apartments, by the alleged members of Lawrence Bishnoi's gang. Over the years, the 31-year-old jailed gangster had issued multiple death threats to the 'Bajrangi Bhaijaan' actor over the 1989 poaching case. For those unversed, Salman was accused of killing a blackbuck - which the Bishnoi community consider as a sacred animal - during the shoot of his film 'Hum Saath Saath Hain' in Rajasthan. Now, according to multiple reports surfacing online, the gang has also allegedly planned to kill popular comedian . As per a Times Now report, Munawar was under their radar for allegedly mocking Hindu gods during his comic stints. For those unversed, the 32-year-old comedian had spent months in jail over his jokes on Hindi religion during one of his stand up shows. Also Read: Here's How Munawar Escaped Lawrence Bishnoi Gang's Planned Death AttackAs per reports, in September, the Lawrence Bishnoi gang allegedly planned a death attack on Munawar while he was attending an event in Delhi. Two gunmen allegedly took the same flight, in which Munawar was flying from Mumbai to Delhi. They had also allegedly booked rooms in rhe same hotel in which Munawar was planning to stay in Delhi. Reportedly, the police received a tip off and escorted the comedian to Mumbai under tight security of Mumbai Police. The Mumbai police has now provided the comedian with security.

Title: Ishq Jabariya Actor Rishaab Chauhaan (Krushna Abhishek's Cousin) Opens Up On Nepotism, Says 'It Might Give...'
Content: Rishaab Chauhaan, who is making his television debut with Sun Neo's "Ishq Jabariya," has captivated the audience with his portrayal of Ritwik, the cousin of Aditya, played by Lakshay Khurana. This role holds a special place in Rishaab's heart, marking a significant step in his acting career. Interestingly, Risha is related to Indian comedian and actor Krushna Abhishek, a connection that brings an intriguing perspective to his journey in the entertainment industry. Rishaab recently opened up about Krushna's reaction to his new role and shared his thoughts on the influence of nepotism in the industry.Rishaab recounted the moment Krushna Abhishek learned of his foray into television with "Ishq Jabariya," expressing joy and support for his cousin's milestone. This reaction highlights the familial bond within the entertainment sphere and showcases how connections can play a role in an artist's career trajectory. However, when delving into the topic of nepotism, Rishaab provided a nuanced take that challenges common perceptions. He argued that while familial ties might offer an initial advantage, they do not ensure lasting success or talent in the industry."In this industry, it's about knowing you have a good friend by your side. If nepotism were the key, there are many big stars whose children haven't been able to achieve much. This field is unique because talent isn't something you can pass on. You can provide financial support, but you can't expect someone to inherit skills. It's like Sachin Tendulkar; his son might not bat as well as him, or he could even be better, but it won't be the same. Krushna didn't know I was doing the show until I started. In this industry, it's best to wait until everything is set before announcing your projects," Rishaab explained, shedding light on the complexity of nepotism's impact.Rishaab further elaborated on nepotism, comparing it to a helpful push that can get someone started but cannot sustain them indefinitely. He emphasized that true talent and perseverance are essential for success, regardless of one's initial advantages. "I believe you can give someone a push, like helping them start on a bicycle, but you can't keep pushing them their whole life. You help them sit, give them that initial push, and as long as someone holds on, they'll keep going. But eventually, you have to let go. A true artist will keep going, and if not, they'll fall off. Nepotism might give someone a start, but it doesn't guarantee stardom. Stars are made; no one can simply declare you a star. There are many big stars whose children haven't made it, while others have done more work. Some haven't even had the chance to pursue acting despite their desires. Nepotism only helps to the extent of giving someone a first chance because they are someone's child," Rishaab shared, offering a candid perspective on the ongoing debate surrounding nepotism in Bollywood."Ishq Jabariya" itself is a romantic drama that enthralls viewers with the story of Gulki, a young woman with dreams bigger than the constraints placed by her controlling stepmother. The narrative weaves through her challenges, ambitions, and the unexpected turns her life takes, possibly leading her to find love in the least expected places. The show, which airs on Sun Neo from Monday to Saturday at 7:30 PM, features a talented cast including Kamya Panjabi, Siddhi Sharma, and Lakshay Khurana in key roles. It presents a compelling story that resonates with many, mirroring the real-life experiences of those navigating their paths in the vast world of entertainment.

Title: Singham Again Box Office Day 3 Prediction: Ajay‚Äôs Cop Drama To See Steady Growth; To Touch 125Cr Today
Content: Singham Again Box Office Collection Day 3 Prediction: Ajay Devgn's recent film Singham Again has finally hit the theatres and we can't keep calm about it. While fans have been in absolute awe of Ajay Devgn reprising his role as Bajirao Singham after 10 years, Ranveer's stint as Simmba also added a lot of masala to the film. Needless to say, Singham Again has managed to open to decent reviews.Singham Again Box Office Collection Day 2According to a report published in Sacnilk, Singham Again made an opening day collection of Rs 43.5 crores on day 1 (first Friday). This was followed by a slight dip in numbers on second day (first Saturday) wherein Singam Again raked in Rs 41.50 crores taking to overall collections of the movie to Rs 85 crores.Singham Again Box Office Collection Day 3 PredictionGiven the ongoing trend, Singham Again is likely to enter the coveted Rs 100 crore club today at the box office. The movie is expected to see steady growth in the collection and is likely to rake in around Rs 40 crores. If the reports turned out to be true, Singham Again is expected to touch Rs 125 crores mark at the box office.Meanwhile, Singham Again will be having a box office clash with Kartik Aaryan and Triptii Dimri's Bhool Bhulaiyaa 3 which is a horror comedy. It will be interesting to see who will win the box office game. Let us know which film you are supporting.

Title: Paradise' Now Streaming On OTT: Where To Watch Roshan Mathew And Darshana Rajendran's Movie
Content: Paradise' Now Streaming on OTT: "Paradise" is a drama film co-produced by Sri Lanka and India, co-written and directed by Prasanna Vithanage. Presented by Mani Ratnam and Siva Ananth under the Madras Talkies banner and produced by Newton Cinema, the film stars Roshan Mathew, Darshana Rajendran, Shyam Fernando, and Mahendra Perera. It revolves around a married couple whose anniversary trip to Sri Lanka takes an unforeseen twist.The film had its global premiere at the 28th Busan International Film Festival on October 7, 2023, where it received the Kim Jiseok Award. It was released in theatres on June 28, 2024.'Paradise' OTT PlatformThe highly anticipated multilingual film "Paradise" is now available for streaming on Amazon Prime Video starting Friday, July 26. Those who missed it in theatres can now enjoy the film from the comfort of their homes.'Paradise' SynopsisAn Indian couple visits the picturesque hill country of crisis-stricken Sri Lanka to celebrate their fifth wedding anniversary. However, unexpected events arise, causing tensions to escalate and revealing deeper rifts in their relationship.'Paradise' Cast and Crew"Paradise" showcases an impressive ensemble cast. Roshan Mathew stars as Kesav, and Darshana Rajendran portrays his wife, Amritha. The couple, an Indian pair, arrives in the scenic but crisis-stricken hill country of Sri Lanka to celebrate their fifth wedding anniversary. As the story unfolds, they meet Shyam Fernando's character, Mr. Andrew, a local tour guide, and Mahendra Perera's Sergeant Bandara, who add depth to their journey. Sumith Ilango plays Shree, and Azher Samsoodeen is Iqbal, both contributing to the evolving narrative as unexpected events escalate tensions and reveal deeper fractures in the couple's relationship. The film explores these characters' interactions, weaving a rich tapestry of human emotions against the backdrop of a nation in turmoil.Directed by Prasanna Vithanage and co-written by Vithanage and Anushka Senanayake, "Paradise" is produced by Sanita Chittilappilly, Anto Chittilappilly, Mani Ratnam, and Siva Ananth. The film features captivating cinematography by Rajeev Ravi and precise editing by A. Sreekar Prasad, with a compelling musical score composed by K. Presented in a trilingual format with dialogue in English, Sinhala, and Malayalam, "Paradise" reflects the diverse cultural backdrop of its setting.

Title: Binny and Family: Karan Johar Praises Ektaa R Kapoor And Mahaveer Jain‚Äôs Film Ahead Of Release
Content: Binny and Family', a slice-of-life film, has garnered significant attention even before its theatrical release. The to commend this family entertainer by Ektaa R Kapoor and Mahaveer Jain is renowned filmmaker Karan Johar. Recently, Mahaveer Jain screened the film for Johar, who was deeply moved by it.Johar shared his thoughts on social media, expressing how the film made him both laugh and cry. He praised the performances and storytelling, particularly the pre-climax sequence.
